Title: Series: Theatrum Pictorium
Description: Plate 213: The flight into Egypt, after Domenico Fetti; with in the centre foreground of a landscape the Virgin and child riding an ass, guided by St Joseph; nearby two putti lying by the roadside. Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Jan van Ossenbeeck
Intermediary draughtsman: David Teniers the Younger
Curator's comments: This is plate 213 from 246 plates of Teniers' Theatre of Paintings, for comment on the series see A,8.1. After the painting in the Kunsthistorisches Museum (inv. GG_155). Also see Safarik, 1990, cat. No.16.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (68)
Weigel 1843 / Suppléments au Peintre-Graveur de Adam Bartsch (307.51)
